# Links Connect Architecture
Version: 0.1.0

Author: Links Industries
Status: Draft

---

# 1. Vision

Links Connect is an industrial telematics platform developed by Links Industries.

The goal is to build a robust, modular and scalable system for monitoring, analyzing and managing machines.

The platform shall support golf equipment, utility vehicles, tractors and future industrial machines.

---

# 2. Mission

Our mission is to reduce downtime, simplify maintenance and provide real-time machine intelligence.

Every machine should be connected.

Every event should be measurable.

Every decision should be data driven.

---

# 3. Design Principles

The following principles apply to the entire project.

## Reliability First

The system must continue operating even if individual modules fail.

## Offline First

Loss of internet connectivity must never stop data collection.

Collected data shall be synchronized automatically once connectivity returns.

## Modular Architecture

Every hardware component shall be isolated behind a common interface.

Replacing a GPS module or adding new sensors must not require rewriting the application.

## Security

Communication must always be authenticated and encrypted.

## Maintainability

Code should be simple, readable and easy to extend.

---

# 4. High-Level Architecture

Links Connect consists of four main parts:

- Agent
- Backend
- Dashboard
- Hardware

The Agent runs on the Raspberry Pi and communicates with hardware devices.

The Backend stores and processes data.

The Dashboard visualizes machine information.

The Hardware layer abstracts GPS, sensors and future peripherals.

---

# 5. Current Prototype

Prototype Version 1 consists of:

- Raspberry Pi 4
- Teltonika RUT950
- USB GPS receiver (planned)
- Battery monitoring (planned)
- Temperature sensors (planned)

---

# 6. Long-Term Goal

Links Connect shall evolve into a complete industrial telematics platform capable of managing thousands of connected machines.
